node.text:
Hey StarReaders! 😉 ⭐ 
We hope you didn't miss our first & second episode from the Star Stable Master Class with author @helenadahlgrenofficial. Here's the first episode for you to learn from now or save for later, to enjoy during your cozy weekend! 📖

If you've already dived into our Star Stable Master Class, we're happy to let you know that Episodes 3 & 4 will come out soon, stay tuned! 🤩

Not only is this Star Stable Master Class full of awesome advice, but we hope it encourages you to write your own story! Put your learnings to the test by joining our ongoing storytelling challenge. Take part in our short
story competition for the chance to have your story turned into an
Instagram comic by illustrator Elli Puukangaas! @ellipuukangas #SSOStoryTellers #ReadWriteUnite

node.title: Star Stable Master Class: From reader to writer

node.text:
Hey StarFam! It's about time that Maya got her own horse! Join her on a very special quest to find her companion. Meanwhile, our seahorse friends have returned to shore!

Maya is well-known around Jorvik for her hard work at Moorland Stables, but her family history has always been shrouded in mystery. Few know the strange circumstances behind the Unfortunate Dews Farm, but now’s your chance to learn! Join Maya on a visit to her ancestral home, learn some family history, and shed some light on this mysterious plot of land. A curious companion awaits. Can you help Maya befriend this mysterious horse?
Meet Maya at the Unfortunate Dews farm to get started. Once you finish this quest, you can start building reputation at the Unfortunate Dews Farm.

Tellina and Kampos are back! These seahorses have arrived on shore just in time for summer! The dazzling blueish Kampos and the pearly Tellina are sure to charm anyone, and don’t miss their Panda Ray pals! They have set up camp by Fort Pinta beach where they will stay for seven weeks! Make sure to go by and say hi! #ISeeSeaHorses
Price:  850 Star Coins each

Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update!

Can you feel the warmth of the sun, the smell of the ocean, and hear the seagulls flying over your head? ☀️ Oh wait, we were talking to our #FriendlyGotlandPony, this cutie is surely enjoying the views! 🌊 

Today the sun is shining on this very particular breed, Sweden’s beloved Gotland Pony! On Jorvik, the breed is a favorite companion for explorers, as the athletic ponies are keen to carry riders across any terrain.

Hungry, stubborn, and loyal, this little fella is basically the Hobbit of the horse world! Find out for yourself what makes the Gotland Pony Sweden’s most popular small breed. #SSOSummer
